{"type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase 11 correctness review is done. Findings are in `phase11-review/findings/correctness.md`.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Overall: needs-fixes** — 0 critical, **2 high**, **5 medium**, **2 low**\n\n### Highest-impact issues\n\n1. **[CORR-001] Canary sends skip SEG content sanitizer** — Real SEG sends go through `sanitizeForSeg()` in `effects.ts`, but `materializeCanarySend()` does not. Canaries can carry different content than production mail, which weakens deliverability signal accuracy.\n\n2. **[CORR-002] `bounced` arrival status never set** — The enum and snapshot SQL support `bounced`, but polling only classifies inbox/spam/quarantine. There is no `In-Reply-To` fallback or NDR detection, so bounces likely become `silent_drop`.\n\n### Other medium findings\n\n- Canary step selection uses `hashToIndex(token)` instead of the injected position (`CORR-003`)\n- `injectionStrategy` config (`first_then_last`, `every_nth`) is accepted but not implemented (`CORR-004`)\n- Canaries bypass `send_reservation` throttle path (`CORR-005`)\n- Snapshot rollup is fixed at 7 days while the grid supports 14/30 days (`CORR-006`)\n\n### What looks solid\n\nRouting decision table (including anchor-threading exception), gateway detection cascade, auto-pause pure logic, `no_safe_mailbox` state machine flow, gateway cache TTL/sweep, SEG throttle + 5-min domain gap inside advisory lock, `isMailboxSafeForGateway`, entry-condition null/unknown handling, and the 24h silent-drop sweep all match the spec.\n\nNo code was changed beyond the findings file."}]},"session_id":"ea6a87f4-c096-4a35-b107-f6ccf68e1181"}
